and then cling on for dear life.

804
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:47,743
So why did you write Paradise Misplaced?

805
00:44:48,102 --> 00:44:51,047
- We don't want to talk about my stuff.
- ANDREA: Yeah, why did you tell that story,

806
00:44:51,147 --> 00:44:52,340
- Mr Michaels?
- How did you come up with that?

807
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:54,884
- Yeah, what was your life raft?
- Did you have a near-death experience?

808
00:44:56,277 --> 00:44:57,549
Oh...

809
00:44:59,447 --> 00:45:01,220
Well, it was a...

810
00:45:02,366 --> 00:45:04,844
I used to tell my son stories at night.

811
00:45:05,369 --> 00:45:06,641
You have a son?

812
00:45:06,787 --> 00:45:07,897
Yeah, yeah, Alex.

813
00:45:07,997 --> 00:45:10,024
He's 18 now

814
00:45:10,124 --> 00:45:12,397
and he is a freshman
at Stanford University.

815
00:45:12,543 --> 00:45:14,236
Wow. So, he's really smart.

816
00:45:14,629 --> 00:45:18,199
Well, his mother was quite clever.
Smart enough to divorce me anyway.

817
00:45:18,299 --> 00:45:20,902
- (ALL CHUCKLE)
- But, while we were still together,

818
00:45:21,594 --> 00:45:23,788
my dad died and...

